A source close to the Sussexes told E! News that the couple were "disappointed" the finding of the investigation will not be shared. Buckingham Palace launched the probe in March last year after it was alleged Meghan drove out two personal assistants and staff were "humiliated" on several occasions. The Duchess's lawyers denied the allegations when they were made. A senior palace source this week said the findings of the inquiry will remain private but changes have been made to the Royal Household's HR policies and procedures which members of the Royal Family and staff have been made aware of. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES ON THE ROYALS: